<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Algonquin Scheduler</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all' %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.3.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
  <% if params[:controller] == "sessions" %>
	  <style>
		  .bg-alg {
			  position: fixed;
			  top: 0;
			  left: 0;
			  background-image: url("/images/ACCE.jpg");
			  background-size: cover;
			  background-position: center center;
			  height: 100%;
			  width: 100%;
		  }
	  </style>
  <% end %>
  <script>
	<% unless session[:current_date].present? %>
		<% session[:current_date] = DateTime.now %>
	<% end %>
	var current_date_from_server = "<%= session[:current_date] %>";

  </script>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application' %>
  <script src="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body ng-app="Scheduler">
<% if params[:controller] == "sessions" %>
	<div class="bg-alg"></div>
<% end %>
<%= yield %>

</body>

<div class="modal fade" id="help-modal">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
	<div class="modal-content">
	  <div class="modal-header">
		<button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
		<h4 class="modal-title">Scheduler Help</h4>
	  </div>
	  <div class="modal-body">
		<p>This is a demo layout for the scheduling application.</p>
		<p>Currently, all users will see the same "meetings" to test the layout without adding extra functionality.</p>
		<p>All data is stored server side, and is representative of what will actually be served to users.</p>
		<p>Upcoming changes:</p>
		<ul>
		  <li>Personalized Events/Schedules</li>
		  <li>Availability Editor (for faculty/staff)</li>
		  <li>Book a meeting</li>
		  <li>Cancel a meeting</li>
		  <li>Book a conference room</li>
		  <li>Day View</li>
		  <li>Month View</li>
		  <li>Course/Class List Uploads</li>
		  <li>Background Processes (Email notifications, etc)</li>
		</ul>

		<p>Current Technology in place:
		<ul>
		  <li>Ruby on Rails 4.2.0 (Server side)</li>
		  <li>AngularJS 1.3 (Client side)</li>
		  <li>MySQL 5</li>
		  <li>nginx</li>
		  <li>Thin Server (will eventually be moved to Unicorn)</li>
		</ul>
		</p>
	  </div>
	</div><!-- /.modal-content -->
  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->
</div><!-- /.modal -->
</html>
